# Source clones — cloned separately per user and not part of the workspace repo
# NOTE: no trailing slash. The same pattern covers both this top-level repos/
# and the real repos/ directory nested inside each work-session's workspace
# worktree, where project worktrees live as siblings.
repos

# Work sessions — the folder and worktrees are local, but the session tracker,
# specs, and plans are tracked so durable thinking travels across machines.
#
# The pattern is intentionally subtle: git cannot re-include files beneath an
# ignored parent directory, so naive `work-sessions/` + `!` negations silently
# fail. Instead:
#   - `work-sessions/**` ignores every descendant at every depth
#   - `!work-sessions/*/` re-includes each session folder as a walkable dir
#   - `!work-sessions/*/session.md` (and friends) re-includes the specific
#     tracked files inside each session folder
# Nested contents like `work-sessions/{name}/workspace/...` stay ignored
# because they are matched by `**` and not re-included.
work-sessions/**
!work-sessions/*/
!work-sessions/*/session.md
!work-sessions/*/design-*.md
!work-sessions/*/plan-*.md

# Disposable workspace-scoped scratchpad (session log, hook debug output)
workspace-scratchpad/

# Personal overrides
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/.active-session.json

# Local-only convention (rules, context)
.claude/rules/local-only-*
shared-context/**/local-only-*

# IDE
.idea/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
